The paper deals with deep learning systems and convolution operations, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus of the paper is on learning convolutions for non-uniformly sampled point clouds, which falls under the category of geometric modeling and processing (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the use of Monte Carlo integration, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and reinforcement learning (cs.AI).
